            <p>
              <b>
                Bloomberg News
              </b>
               (originally 
              <b>
                Bloomberg Business News
              </b>
              ), is an international 
              <a href="/wiki/News_agency" title="News agency">
                news agency
              </a>
               headquartered in 
              <a href="/wiki/New_York_City" title="New York City">
                New York
              </a>
               and a 
              <a href="/wiki/Division_(business)" title="Division (business)">
                division
              </a>
               of 
              <a href="/wiki/Bloomberg_L.P." title="Bloomberg L.P.">
                Bloomberg L.P.
              </a>
               Content produced by Bloomberg News is disseminated through 
              <a href="/wiki/Bloomberg_Terminal" title="Bloomberg Terminal">
                Bloomberg Terminals
              </a>
              , 
              <a href="/wiki/Bloomberg_Television" title="Bloomberg Television">
                Bloomberg Television
              </a>
              , 
              <a href="/wiki/Bloomberg_Radio" title="Bloomberg Radio">
                Bloomberg Radio
              </a>
              , 
              <i>
                <a href="/wiki/Bloomberg_Businessweek" title="Bloomberg Businessweek">
                  Bloomberg Businessweek
                </a>
              </i>
              , 
              <i>
                <a href="/wiki/Bloomberg_Markets" title="Bloomberg Markets">
                  Bloomberg Markets
                </a>
              </i>
              , Bloomberg.com and Bloomberg's mobile platforms. Since 2015, 
              <a href="/wiki/John_Micklethwait" title="John Micklethwait">
                John Micklethwait
              </a>
               has served as 
              <a href="/wiki/Editor-in-chief" title="Editor-in-chief">
                editor-in-chief
              </a>
              .
              <sup id="cite_ref-Greenberg_2-0" class="reference">
                <a href="#cite_note-Greenberg-2">
                  [2]
                </a>
              </sup>
            </p>
